        h3 Requirements

        p Students are required to have strong foundations on algorithms, databases and software engineering. They are also required to have BlueSky and github accounts. Please #[a(href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScyXIReQa7p3HmusYEKc2pLIbklf-3Y__-mZMG7DALhrLK9OQ/viewform?usp=sf_link") use this form to enter your BlueSky and Github handle]
        p Every student is required to complete a #[a(href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1QLF2AezyeRHaSldqc_m2y4wvV4-J0IzVik-Xtw7bU9w/edit?usp=sharing") series of readings and materials before class]. This is not only #[strong required] but also very important, since in class we will assume they were reviewed, discuss them and cover more advanced topics.


        h4 Reading comments
        p #[strong Before every class, students must tweet something they learned from the readings with the hashtag #WebDev and the handle @NortheasternCA]. The comments should be original, shouldn't repeat what was said before, and demonstrate the proficiency of the required reading.
          p These tweets are going to considered for the class participation grade. Each comment will be rated as follows:
          ul
            li #[strong 2 points]: An interesting and original comment
            li #[strong 1 points]: An interesting comment but that was mentioned before by another student
            li #[strong 0 points]: A non interesting comment

